            <div xml:id="vicavExplBar_dualApproach">
                <head>Dual Approach</head>
                
                <p>The VICAV website is designed in a manner supposed to allow users to investigate 
                    the available resources through various methods. The basic access mode is to 
                    launch a query by clicking on the symbols on the map.</p>
                
                <p>There are two distinct symbols: arrows and circles. The arrows indicate particular 
                    locations (towns, parts of towns, villages), the circles are used for regions 
                    that can but do not necessarily correlate with countries. </p>
                
                <p>
                    <graphic url="vicav_locations_regions.jpg"/>
                </p>
                
                <p>However, most queries can also be triggered by clicking on menu items or by formulating explicit queries.</p>
                <p>
                    <graphic url="vicav_query__001.jpg"/>
                </p>
            </div>
            
        </body>
